ِ

Borrowed from Arabic كَسْرَة‎ (kasra, “a breaking”), instance noun from the verbal noun كَسْر‎ (kasr, “breaking”) of the verb كَسَرَ‎ (kasara, “to break”).

Examples	
دِ (di) /di/.
دِي (dī)/diː/.

kasra (plural kasras)

In Arabic script, the vowel point for "i", appearing as a small diagonal line placed below a letter ( ـِ ) and designating a short i /i/. If the Arabic letter ي‎ (yāʾ) immediately follows, it indicates a long ī /iː/.
